# 🧩 Humanized AI – Project Plan

## 🚀 Project Overview
**Humanized AI** is an AI-powered web and mobile platform designed to make digital interactions more natural and human-like.  
It integrates AI automation, machine learning, and Web3 technology to enhance personalization, ensure data transparency, and support user data ownership.

The project aims to create a bridge between **AI intelligence** and **human empathy**, making technology easier to interact with while preserving privacy and trust.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
1. Develop an intelligent AI assistant that understands natural language and user intent.  
2. Integrate decentralized identity and data management using Web3 principles.  
3. Build a user-friendly web dashboard and mobile interface.  
4. Deploy the platform for public use and further open-source contribution.

---

## 🗓️ Project Milestones & Deliverables

| Phase | Duration | Description | Deliverables |
|-------|-----------|--------------|---------------|
| **Milestone 1** | 1 Month | **Design & Setup** — Define architecture, system design, and core structure. | Architecture document, UI mockups, GitHub repo setup |
| **Milestone 2** | 2 Months | **Core Development** — Build backend APIs, AI logic, and integrate database. | AI chatbot engine, backend APIs, initial frontend |
| **Milestone 3** | 1 Month | **Web3 Integration** — Implement decentralized login & data ownership. | Web3 wallet connection, Polkadot/Substrate module |
| **Milestone 4** | 1 Month | **Testing & Beta Launch** — Perform QA testing and prepare for launch. | Beta release, test reports, community feedback |
| **Milestone 5** | Ongoing | **Public Launch & Maintenance** | Official release, updates, and open-source contribution |

